fect calculations.\n- C: understands complicated technology, quick correct decisions, calm in crisis. Egocentric, difficulty communicating.\n- D: concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, responds to unexpected events. Good technical problem solving.\n\nCalmness, judgment, performance under pressure:\n- A: not explicit calmness, but can anticipate dangerous situations (good judgment). No mention of stress handling.\n- B: handles stress very well (good).\n- C: keeps calm in a crisis (good), quick decisions.\n- D: hot temper (negative), but responds adequately to unexpected events.\n\nSound and timely decision-making:\n- A: sees complex connections, anticipates danger (good decision-making). Not explicit speed.\n- B: handles stress, but no decision-making mention.\n- C: makes correct decisions quickly (strong).\n- D: solves problems extremely well (implies good decisions), but hot temper may affect timeliness.\n\nTeamwork, communication, crew cooperation:\n- A: very good leadership qualities (positive), but regarded as show-off and not open to new ideas (negative for teamwork). No explicit communication.\n- B: none positive, negative interpersonal (grumpy, nasty remarks).\n- C: creates positive atmosphere with crew (positive), but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric.\n- D: no explicit teamwork, negative know-it-all, hot temper.\n\nProfessional development and long-term suitability:\n- A: not open to new ideas (negative for development).\n- B: excellent computer skills, conscientious, but weak memory for numbers, nasty remarks may hinder growth.\n- C: not willing to further education (negative), egocentric.\n- D: hot temper, know-it-all (negative), but takes responsibility seriously.\n\nNow weigh overall. For long-distance flights, key: reliability, calmness under prolonged stress, good decision-making, teamwork/communication (crew coordination), technical competence (navigation, weather, systems), ability to handle fatigue, continuous learning.\n\nCand